cs.MA, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a package delivery scheme that utilizes ridesharing systems, which involves multiple agents (taxis, passengers, and packages) interacting with each other. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses Multivariate Gauss distribution and Bayesian inference to predict passenger orders. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes an intelligent solution for package delivery. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the computation efficiency and solution effectiveness of the proposed solution. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the logistics of city-wide package delivery, which involves the transportation network and the information flow between different agents.
